<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Re-description female</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 33, 34" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figures 33, 34. Mesembrius spp., habitus, lateral view 33 M. maculifer Hull (♀) 34 M. madagascariensis Keiser (♀)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1046.57052.figures33-34" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/557478" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">33</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Body length: 11.2 mm. Wing length: 8.7 mm. (Only female paratype measured).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Head</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 70–74" captionStartId="F28" captionText="Figures 70 - 74. Mesembrius spp., head, frontal view 70 M. capensis (Macquart) (♀) 71 M. cyanipennis (Bezzi) (♀) 72 M. chapini Curran (♀) 73 M. maculifer Hull (♀) 74 M. morio (Bezzi) (♀)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1046.57052.figures70-74" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/557489" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">73</figureCitation>
). Eyes bare, dichoptic. Face chocolate-brown to mahogany-red. Frons with ventral 2/3 light yellow-brown pilose. Face very short reddish pubescent; sparsely long pale pilose. Ocellar triangle bare. Frontal triangle with a transverse band of dark pile. Occiput chocolate-brown to mahogany-red; thick dark brown pilose. Antenna dark reddish-brown; arista paler.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Thorax.</emphasis>
Dull black; lateral margins and scutellum very dark red; pleurites black; reddish-orange pilose. Scutellum dull black; white pilose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Legs.</emphasis>
Predominantly black, the distal part of the pro- and mesolegs dark red; all tibiae dark red; all tarsi black dorsally, the hind pair rather flattened. Pile pale whitish on tarsi and tibiae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Wing</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 135–138" captionStartId="F41" captionText="Figures 135 - 138. Mesembrius spp., right wing 135 M. maculifer Hull (♀) 136 M. madagascariensis Keiser (♂) 137 M. minor (Bezzi) (♂) 138 M. morio (Bezzi) (♀)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1046.57052.figures135-138" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/557502" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">135</figureCitation>
). Proximal half of the wing deep brown, especially at the r-m crossvein.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Abdomen</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 113–118" captionStartId="F36" captionText="Figures 113 - 118. Mesembrius spp., abdomen, dorsal view 113 M. cyanipennis (Bezzi) (♀) 114 M. maculifer Hull (♀) 115 M. madagascariensis Keiser (♀) 116 M. minor (Bezzi) (♀) 117 M. morio (Bezzi) (♀) 118 M. platytarsis Curran syn. nov. (♀)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1046.57052.figures113-118" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/557497" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">114</figureCitation>
). Dull black. Tergite II with a pair of prominent light-yellow maculae; white pilose anteriorly, light reddish pilose posteriorly. Tergite III and IV dark brown to black; light reddish pilose, but blackish on the middle of the posterior part.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
